==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Admixture
<hw>Ad*mix"ture</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>admiscere</ets>, <ets>admixtum</ets>, to admix; <ets>ad</ets> +
<ets>miscere</ets> to mix. See <er>Mix</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of mixing; mixture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The compound formed by mixing different substances
together.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which is mixed with anything.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Admonish</ent>⟦br⟧
